		<div id="comment_body_64675434"><p>That's insufficient, actually.  Natural carbon sequestration processes are too slow, we need to both stop burning hydrocarbons AND start artificial carbon sequestration projects.</p><p>But even that might be a bad thing - ecosystems react poorly to rapid change, and if we could return CO2 levels to those of the pre-industrial era faster than we raised them, that could cause more extinctions.</p><p>It's a big problem, requiring big solutions, and none of the solutions can actually fix the issue the way we'd like to see it<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
